full_text: Screened by NARA, 7/20/2023 BIRTH CERTIFICATE The undersigned Municipal Civil Registrar certifies: That in the Civil Registry book of births that is in the archives of this municipality, is found the birth certificate #00036, placed in Folio #167, Volume #3 and that belongs to: MANUEL DE JESUS -- in the town of Sinuapa, on the 7th day of the month of May 1910. Before me: Jesus Madrid, Municipal Secretary of this population and before the witnesses: Mr. Manuel Fuentes, of legal age, and Mr. Manuel Chinchilla, of legal age, Hondurans, of this neighborhood. Appeared personally Mrs. Jesus Diaz, giving account that on January 10th of the current year (1910) was born in the house of Mr. Aquilino Pena, a boy whom they called: Manuel De Jesus. Natural son of the denouncer of domestic duties occupation of this neighborhood. Maternal Grandmother, Maria Diaz. I read the written to the denouncer and witnesses, manifesting that she was illiterate (could not sign) Jesus Madrid, secretary -- Manuel Chinchilla Manuel Fuentes Extended in the town council of Sinuapa, Ocotepeque, on the 4th day of the month of October 1990. Doris Elizabeth Espinoza R.C.M. Translated by Linda Matta. I am fluent bilingual (Spanish / English). To the best of my knowledge, this document is accurate in its translation and equal to its Spanish original copy. Signature: Linda Matta Date: 12/10/91 STATE OF CALIFORNIA OFFICIAL SEAL ELIVIA BENITEZ NOTARY PUBLIC - CALIFORNIA LOS ANGELES COUNTY COUNTY OF Los Angeles My comm. expires AUG 24, 1993 SubscRibed and SWORN before me on This 13TH, DAY OF December OF 1991, Eawwa Receively
